Makes: 2 x 400g jars.Ingredients:2kg onions, thinly sliced4 cloves of garlic, sliced180g butter60ml (4 tbsp) olive oil140g brown sugar15ml (1 tbsp) finely chopped rosemarySalt and freshly ground black pepper250ml (1 cup) wine vinegarMethod:1) Combine the onions and garlic in a heavy-based pan with the butter and oil.2) Cook over a gentle heat till the onions are soft but not browned, about 10 minutes.3) Add the sugar, rosemary and seasoning; cook till the sugar has been absorbed then simmer for 30 minutes.4) Add the vinegar and cook for another 15 minutes till soft and sticky.5) Store in glass jars in the fridge and use as required.